  "body": "If full-sync fails without having done a flush to disk, it will switch over to fast-sync next time it's started\r\n\r\n```\r\n[user@work go-ethereum]$ build/bin/geth --syncmode full\r\nINFO [03-02|21:01:36.907] Maximum peer count                       ETH=25 LES=0 total=25\r\nINFO [03-02|21:01:36.908] Starting peer-to-peer node               instance=Geth/v1.9.0-unstable-f9aa1cd2/linux-amd64/go1.11.2\r\nINFO [03-02|21:01:36.908] Allocated trie memory caches             clean=256.00MiB dirty=256.00MiB\r\n\r\n... panic (my bad)...\r\n```\r\nRecompile, fix `panic`, and start over:\r\n```\r\n[user@work go-ethereum]$ build/bin/geth --syncmode full\r\nINFO [03-02|21:08:20.871] Maximum peer count                       ETH=25 LES=0 total=25\r\nINFO [03-02|21:08:20.872] Starting peer-to-peer node               instance=Geth/v1.9.0-unstable-f9aa1cd2/linux-amd64/go1.11.2\r\nINFO [03-02|21:08:20.872] Allocated trie memory caches             clean=256.00MiB dirty=256.00MiB\r\nINFO [03-02|21:08:20.872] Allocated cache and file handles         database=/home/user/.ethereum/geth/chaindata cache=512.00MiB handles=2048\r\nINFO [03-02|21:08:22.280] Initialised chain configuration          config=\"{ChainID: 1 Homestead: 1150000 DAO: 1920000 DAOSupport: true EIP150: 2463000 EIP155: 2675000 EIP158: 2675000 Byzantium: 4370000 Constantinople: 7280000  ConstantinopleFix: 7280000 Engine: ethash}\"\r\nINFO [03-02|21:08:22.280] Disk storage enabled for ethash caches   dir=/home/user/.ethereum/geth/ethash count=3\r\nINFO [03-02|21:08:22.280] Disk storage enabled for ethash DAGs     dir=/home/user/.ethash               count=2\r\nINFO [03-02|21:08:22.280] Initialising Ethereum protocol           versions=\"[63 62]\" network=1 dbversion=4\r\nWARN [03-02|21:08:22.303] Head state missing, repairing chain      number=46401 hash=6cc737…40b080\r\nINFO [03-02|21:08:23.537] Rewound blockchain to past state         number=0     hash=d4e567…cb8fa3\r\nINFO [03-02|21:08:23.537] Loaded most recent local header          number=46401 hash=6cc737…40b080 td=43055236701273795 age=3y7mo1w\r\nINFO [03-02|21:08:23.537] Loaded most recent local full block      number=0     hash=d4e567…cb8fa3 td=17179869184       age=49y10mo2w\r\nINFO [03-02|21:08:23.537] Loaded most recent local fast block      number=46401 hash=6cc737…40b080 td=43055236701273795 age=3y7mo1w\r\nINFO [03-02|21:08:23.538] Loaded local transaction journal         transactions=0 dropped=0\r\nINFO [03-02|21:08:23.538] Regenerated local transaction journal    transactions=0 accounts=0\r\n\r\n```\r\nSince the full block was never stored, but the fastblock was, `geth` now ignores my command to do a full-sync, and instead proceeds with a fast-sync. \r\n\r\nThe hacky fix to get around it is to do a `geth removedb`, but that's not the Correct Way (tm). ",
